column1: Oxygen Isotope Records Assimilated
Released July 2020
Correction Description:
SMOW = Standard Mean Ocean Water
latflow = latitude difference between the site of snow deposition and the ice-core site
elevflow = elevation difference between the site of snow deposition and the ice-core site
The corrections were implemented in the order that they are listed.
Units:
Time is in years before 1950 CE (BP).
Oxygen isotope ratios (d18O) are given as per mil deviations relative to the mean for the reference period.
Values are for the middle of the interval. For example the value at time 100 BP is the average over time 75 to 125 BP.
The timescales are all equivalent to the GICC05 timescale except for the Dye3 timescale prior to 11700 BP.
Missing data = -999999
Reference for Anomaly:
mean over 100 to -50 BP
